args: Thank you for agreeing to escort me,\nYour Highness.
Think nothing of it. I would be remiss\nif I didn't do all I could to ensure the\nsafety of an Ilian priest.
As a Paladyn, it is my honor\nto serve you as well, Father.
...Wait. I sense someone in the shadows\nof that tree!
So you've come for the priest's life,\nheathen scum? Prepare yourselves!
I am unharmed. And you, Father?
I'm fine as well. Although sadly,\nthis confirms radicals in the Church\nare targeting me. How terrifying!
Don't worry. We'll keep you safe.
We are fortunate to have someone with\nyour sharp senses at our side, Alex.
(Something is wrong. It's like they\nwere waiting to ambush us.)
(Was our route leaked? Are we made?\nIf we get attacked on a path this narrow...)
Bwaaa ha ha! Lookit who showed up!\nThey're fish in a barrel from here!
I'll take out the Paladyn AND the prince,\nand walk outta here with my pockets\nstuffed with gold!
Face the consequences of your mistakes.
What happened, Alex? We were worried\nwhen we couldn't find you.
An assassin who was lying in wait ahead.\nI fear our route has been leaked.
As none but those of our party knew the\nroute, I fear there is a traitor in our midst.

I heard this cur mention receiving a
reward for killing both a prince and a
Paladynâ€”which means the assassins
aren't targeting the priest after all.
Instead, this is a trap to kill Elisanne\nand  {player_name}.
And our traitor is none other than...\nthe priest himself!
I assure you, child, I am no traitor!
Don't move! I know there is a knife\nconcealed on your person.
The sin of betrayal is great indeed.\nI hope you are ready to pay a heavy price.
The only traitor here is YOU!

After all the kindness Father Nikolai
showed you, you still chose to betray
him! No amount of repentance is
sufficient for your heinous crimes!
Filthy heathen! Bow down before\nthe goddess's almighty power!
Are you all right, Your Highness?!
Just a scratch. I'll be fine.
This is all because you took the blow\nintended for me, {player_name}.
I would do the same for any friend.\nEr, but why didn't you just dodge so I\ndidn't have to do that in the first place?
Is it something to do with this\nFather Nikolai person?
I don't belong with you after all...
Tell us what's bothering you, Alex.
This problem is mine alone.\nIt has naught to do with you.
Of course it has to do with us!\nWe're friends!
I told you never to think of me\nas a friend.
If you knew the horrors of my past,\nyou would never call me by that name.
That is simply not true, Alex.\nNow tell us what happened!
If the past is a burden to you,\nallow us to lighten your load.
Very well. Listen, then, as I tell you of\nthe sins I will bear for the rest of my days.
Hey, stay with me! Damn it,\nthis wasn't supposed to happen...
Oh my, look at all this blood...\nI saw what you did to that man,\nyou know.
Th-that wasn't meant to happen!\nI wasn't trying to...to...
Heh heh. Oh, I know he sought\nto commit violence against you.
And yet, that does not change the sin\nyou have committed in taking a life.
The Church may be merciful, but it does\nnot shelter murderers, you know.
But if I'm driven from the Church,\nI'll go back to being...
Ah, but I would not be a true man of the\ncloth if I did not offer a path to salvation\nto one so wretched.
Help me, child! Aid me in punishing\nheretical followers of the Church!
Do not worry yourself on their behalf.\nSuch hopeless fools deserve to atone\nwith their very lives.
Or do you think there is another path\nfor a filthy sinner like yourself?
...I was scared of losing my place in the\nworld, and so became the Church's puppet.
You were put in an impossible position\nand have nothing to feel guilty for.
Perhaps at first. But after a while, I started\ntelling myself what I was doing was right\nin order to ESCAPE that guilt.
This is all a result of the weakness and\nugliness in my heart. It is my sin to bear.
I came to this castle in the thought that\neven a wretched sinner like myself might\nhave some small part to play.
But now I know that was folly;\none such as me has no place here.
I know how you must feel, Alex,\nbut I assure you that is untrue.
It pains me to see you suffer so!
I think you should wait and think before\nmaking your decision, Alex.
I shall help you think about it.\nNay, we ALL shall!
I will tarry here a while longer.
And I will use that time to think about how\nto atone for my countless sins.
